**Category:** essay-draft truth aristotle aquinas knowledge correspondence practical-knowledge

**Abstract:**
Essay titled "On the Notion of Truth and that Truth is One" examining how truth became identified with correspondence of mind to reality. Traces the anomaly that Aristotle attributes material truth to animal perception while denying formal truth. Critiques the pictorial model of knowledge and the coherence requirement ("the truth is one") that creates conflicts between theology and physics. Proposes practical knowledge as alternative where knowledge is intrinsically connected to action.

**AI Recommendation:** Central epistemological text; relates to 97-JUL-1, 97-NOV-1.

